# As Many as You Need

You can have unlimited elif blocks:

```python
if cond1:
    ...
elif cond2:
    ...
elif cond3:
    ...
elif cond4:
    ...
elif cond5:
    ...
else:
    ...
```

But consider using a dictionary for many cases!

slides.codeSnippet:
temperature = 25
humidity = 60

if temperature > 30 and humidity > 70:
    weather = "Hot and humid"
elif temperature > 30:
    weather = "Hot and dry"
elif temperature > 20:
    weather = "Warm and pleasant"
elif temperature > 10:
    weather = "Cool"
else:
    weather = "Cold"

print(f"Weather: {weather}")
